        <li>After securing the housing halves, check switches and buttons for proper function, then install the battery and verify operation.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Tool will not start</td>
            <td>Battery discharged or not latched</td>
            <td>Recharge or reseat the battery; confirm the fuel gauge shows charge</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Runs but pad does not spin / poor finish</td>
            <td>Excessive downward pressure</td>
            <td>Reduce pressure and let the tool&rsquo;s weight do the work</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Swirl marks or gouges</td>
            <td>Tool lifted/lowered while triggered, or worn abrasive</td>
            <td>Start and stop the tool off the work; replace worn discs; step through grits</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Poor dust collection</td>
            <td>Full dust bag, clogged pad holes, or loose vacuum hose</td>
            <td>Empty the bag, align/clear the pad holes, secure the vacuum adapter</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Disc will not stay attached</td>
            <td>Worn hook-and-loop backing pad</td>
            <td>Replace the backing pad (44-52-1007)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Tool stops and feels hot</td>
            <td>Overload / thermal protection</td>
            <td>Reduce load and allow the tool and battery to cool before resuming</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

